Title : Albert Manent
Text : '''Albert Manent i Segimon''' (23 September 1930 &ndash; 14 April 2014) was a [[Spain|Spanish]] writer and cultural activist. He was mostly involved in the field of [[Catalan language|Catalan]]. Manent was the son of the writer [[Marià Manent]]. He graduated the subject of law and in Catalan [[philology]]. He was born in [[Premia de Dalt]], Spain.

In 1995 he won the [[Ramon Llull Novel Award]] for his biography ''Marià Manent, biografía íntima i literària''.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://elpais.com/diario/1995/03/10/cultura/794790005_850215.html |title=Albert Manent gana el Premio Ramon Llull con una biografía de su padre |trans-title=Albert Manent Wins the Ramon Llull Award with a Biography of His Father |first=Xavier |last=Moret |work=[[El País]] |location=Barcelona |language=Spanish |date=10 March 1995 |access-date=21 May 2019}}</ref>

Manent died in [[Madrid]] from an illness, aged 83.<ref>[http://www.lavanguardia.com/cultura/20140414/54405820774/muere-albert-manent-premi-honor-lletres-catalanes.html La Vanguardia.com: Muere Albert Manent, Premi d'Honor de les Lletres Catalanes]</ref><ref>[http://ccaa.elpais.com/ccaa/2014/04/15/catalunya/1397517039_649724.html El País: Muere Albert Manent, clave en la trastienda cultural catalana]</ref>

